      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Skipping your basal dose is a decision you should only make after consulting with your doctor, as it can be risky. Basal insulin is designed to keep your blood sugar stable throughout the day and night, regardless of your meal intake. If you've had a very light meal, you might need to adjust your basal, but completely skipping it could lead to a dangerous low. It's always best to check with your healthcare provider for personalized advice.",
